# data-models

## Core Data Models

### Meetings Model
Importance Score: 95

Primary business entity representing organizational meetings with:
- Unique signal extraction categories (decisions, action items, blockers, risks)
- Screenshot collection with contextual metadata
- Multi-source transcript integration (Pocket + Teams)
- Structured signal relationships to related entities
- 24-hour expiration window for conversation history
- Weighted command tracking with frequency/recency metrics
- Domain-specific categorization (sprints, tickets, standups)

### Documents Model
Importance Score: 90

Knowledge base documents with:
- Business domain tagging system
- Hierarchical relationship mapping
- Time-based data organization with burndown tracking
- Signal extraction patterns
- Context-aware categorization

## Model Relationships

### Meeting-Signal Flow
- Meetings contain extracted signals
- Signals link to source meetings
- Hierarchical signal promotion system
- Status tracking workflow (pending/approved/rejected/archived)

### Document-Meeting Context
- Documents reference related meetings
- Bi-directional relationship tracking
- Context preservation across entities
- Domain-specific tag clustering

